Whois is appropiate if we run it in a administrative structure similar
to domains.  At Stanford we run a whois server which contains all the
information about people and machines at Stanford. It runs on one of
our primary domain servers and is accessible throughout the Internet.
It is connected to the registration system which in turns creates
tables for domain-servers, /etc/hosts for machines that still use them,
and talbes for other protocols.

			Abraham Bleiberg

